HEADWORD: Cribellum
<hw>Cri*bel"lum</hw> <pr>(kr?b?l"l?m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
a small sieve, dim. of <ets>cribrum</ets> sieve.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A peculiar perforated organ of certain spiders
(<fam>Ciniflonid⟦ae⟧</fam>), used for spinning a special kind of
silk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cribrate</ent>⟦br⟧
